      "amount": "1/2 teaspoon"
    },
    {
      "name": "corn husks",
      "amount": "4-6",
      "notes": "fresh or dried"
    }
  ],
  "instructions": [
    "Preheat the oven to 400 degrees Fahrenheit.",
    "In a large bowl, whisk together olive oil, garlic, paprika, salt, and black pepper.",
    "Add the chicken breast to the bowl and coat with the marinade.",
    "Wrap the chicken in foil and roast for 30 minutes.",
    "While the chicken is cooking, caramelize the onions in a pan over medium heat.",
    "Add the bouquet garni to the pan and cook for an additional 5 minutes.",
    "Once the chicken is done, let it rest for 10 minutes before slicing.",
    "Assemble the wraps by placing sliced chicken and caramelized onions onto a corn husk.",
    "Serve immediately and enjoy.",
    "Cook poultry to an internal temperature of 74°C / 165°F before serving."
